01:27.887 --> 01:32.620
## [ Continues ]

01:41.101 --> 01:45.162
## [ Song Ends ]

01:45.271 --> 01:48.638
- [ Crowd Cheering ]
- Thank you, Springfield! I love you! Peace!

01:48.741 --> 01:52.336
<i>[ Man On Speaker ] Thank you,</i>
<i>Cyndi Lauper.Just a reminder, folks.</i>

01:52.445 --> 01:55.642
- <i>We do have a baseball game today.</i>
- Oh, right.

01:55.748 --> 02:00.208
I'm Dennis Conroy.
And here come your Isotopes.

02:00.320 --> 02:02.618
- [ Crowd Booing ]
- [ Coughing ]

02:02.722 --> 02:05.156
Let's welcome two new additions
to the team...

02:05.258 --> 02:07.783
<i>Smash Diggins and Fishbone Walker.</i>

02:07.894 --> 02:10.657
<i>Lucky for us, they were</i>
<i>sent down from the majors...</i>

02:10.763 --> 02:12.663
<i>for drug violations.</i>

02:12.765 --> 02:13.993
- <i>[ Crowd Cheering ]</i>
- <i>##[ Organ Fanfare ]</i>

02:21.141 --> 02:23.439
Why do you hate the Isotopes
so much, Dad?

02:23.543 --> 02:26.011
Because I loved them once
and they broke my heart.

02:26.112 --> 02:29.013
Let that be a lesson to you,
sweetie. Never love anything.

02:29.115 --> 02:31.379
- Even you?
- Especially me.

02:31.484 --> 02:33.384
But you gotta support the team, Dad.

02:33.486 --> 02:35.920
They're already threatening
to move to MooseJaw.

02:36.022 --> 02:38.047
That's right.
Like my mother always said...

02:38.158 --> 02:41.457
you've gotta stick it out,
even if you picked a loser.

02:41.561 --> 02:44.121
- Hmm.
- To the bitter end.

02:44.230 --> 02:46.323
<i>[ Conroy On Speaker ]</i>
<i>First pitch of the game.</i>

02:46.432 --> 02:49.333
- [ Screaming ]
- <i>That's a rotator cuff.</i>

02:49.435 --> 02:51.426
- <i>His career's over.</i>
- I'm gonna warm up the car.

02:51.538 --> 02:54.098
- But there's only been one pitch.
- And it sucked.

02:54.207 --> 02:58.507
<i>Bases loaded, two outs,</i>
<i>bottom of the ninth, and it's do or die.</i>

02:58.611 --> 03:00.841
## [ Homer Singing ]

03:00.947 --> 03:03.438
That'll bring up Babe Ruth IV.

03:03.550 --> 03:05.711
<i>Of course,</i>
<i>he's no Babe Ruth III...</i>

03:05.818 --> 03:10.778
<i>but the franchise is very excited about</i>
<i>this illegitimate great grand bambino.</i>

03:10.890 --> 03:15.224
<i>And what's this? He's pointing</i>
<i>to the right field bleachers.</i>

03:15.328 --> 03:17.455
<i>Probably at a dying little boy.</i>

03:17.564 --> 03:20.727
- Mom, am I dying?
- No, of course not.

03:20.833 --> 03:23.927
- Is he, Mom? You can tell me.
- No!

03:24.037 --> 03:26.232
<i>[ Conroy ]</i>
<i>Now he's pointing to the ground.</i>

03:26.339 --> 03:29.001
<i>Is he indicating a bunt?</i>
<i>Yes, he's bunting.!</i>

03:29.108 --> 03:31.599
- [ Players Groaning ]
- [ Crowd Booing ]

03:31.711 --> 03:33.611
<i>[ Marge ]</i>
<i>Good hustle, kid.!</i>

03:33.713 --> 03:35.738
## [ Homer Singing ]

03:35.848 --> 03:39.181
- So who won? The losers?
- No, they lost.

03:39.285 --> 03:42.379
- [ Chuckles ] Losers.
- But only by two points.

03:42.488 --> 03:47.084
They didn't resort to stealing bases like
the other team, so it's kind of a moral victory.

03:47.193 --> 03:50.321
With a little middle relief,
they might even make the play-offs.

03:50.430 --> 03:53.888
You'll be in your cold, cold
grave before that ever happens.

03:54.000 --> 03:57.800
Homer, would you please stop talking
about the children's graves?

03:57.904 --> 04:00.168
<i>[ Crowd Chattering ]</i>

04:00.273 --> 04:02.639
[ Laughs ]
All right! Whoo!

04:02.742 --> 04:04.642
[ Grunts ]
What's the hubbub?

04:04.744 --> 04:06.769
Did Moe finally blow his brains out?

04:06.879 --> 04:08.972
Quiet! We're watching the Isotopes.

04:09.082 --> 04:11.141
<i>Shut it off.</i>
<i>They're losers.</i>

04:11.251 --> 04:13.242
Where you been?
The Isotopes are on fire.

04:13.353 --> 04:17.221
Yeah, that sniper at the all-star game
was a blessing in disguise.

04:17.322 --> 04:19.382
Now we're in the championship game.

04:19.492 --> 04:21.392
Championship? Hmm.

04:22.795 --> 04:26.162
Whoo! 'Topes rule!

04:26.266 --> 04:28.393
- [ Gulping ]
- Well, here's a die-hard fan.

04:28.501 --> 04:31.902
Sir, your beloved Isotopes are
about to make history. Any thoughts?

04:32.005 --> 04:35.304
Oh, it's a great team, Kent.
We never gave up hope.

04:35.408 --> 04:39.469
I want to thankJesus
and say hi to my special lady, Marge.

04:39.579 --> 04:42.844
We did it, baby!
Whoo! Whoo!

04:42.949 --> 04:47.852
The inspiring words of a fan who'll always
root, root, root for the home team.

04:47.954 --> 04:51.151
- Even if they lose this game.
- They lost? Those losers!

04:51.257 --> 04:53.521
No, no, no.
The game's not over.

04:53.626 --> 04:56.390
Whoo! Not over! Whoo!

04:56.496 --> 04:59.329
There you have it- ''Whoo.''

04:59.432 --> 05:01.992
- Here it comes, baby. Real big one!
- [ All Shouting ]

05:02.101 --> 05:06.060
<i>[ Conroy On Speaker ] Bottom of the ninth,</i>
<i>two outs. It all comes down to this.</i>

05:06.172 --> 05:08.538
- <i>And here's the pitch.</i>
- <i>[ Bat Strikes Ball ]</i>

05:08.641 --> 05:11.542
<i>Humpin' ''hay-zeus';!</i>
<i>He got all of that one.!</i>

05:11.644 --> 05:15.205
- It's going, going, going-
- [ All Gasping ]

05:15.315 --> 05:17.681
Our technical director today
was Stan Kadlubowski.

05:17.784 --> 05:20.184
<i>It's out ofhere.!</i>
<i>'Topes win.!</i>

05:20.286 --> 05:23.255
- [ All Cheering ]
- Isotopes!

05:23.356 --> 05:26.723
<i>What'd I tell you?</i>
<i>Isotopes.! Whoo.!</i>

05:26.826 --> 05:29.226
[ Gulping ]

05:29.329 --> 05:32.890
- Ah, nobody touched my rumaki.
- <i>[ Screams ] Rumaki.!</i>

05:32.999 --> 05:36.935
- Yea! Isotopes!
- [ Horn Honking ]

05:37.036 --> 05:39.231
- Whoo!
- [ Grunting ]

05:39.339 --> 05:43.207
- Isotopes! [ Grunts ]
- Isotopes!

05:43.309 --> 05:47.302
- <i>[ Horn Continues Honking ]</i>
- <i>Isotopes.! You know what I'm sayin'to you, baby?</i>

05:47.413 --> 05:51.213
Hey! A baseball field!
Batter up!

05:51.317 --> 05:53.512
- [ Cheering ]
- Go, baby!

05:53.619 --> 05:55.519
- Steal second!
- I think I'm gonna puke!

05:55.621 --> 05:57.555
- Hey, who's on first?
- Touchdown!

05:57.657 --> 06:00.421
- <i>[ Barney Yelling ]</i>
- [ Tires Screeching ]

06:01.494 --> 06:05.123
- <i>[ Homer ] Safe.!</i>
- [ All Whooping ]

06:07.433 --> 06:11.301
- Hey, Carl? Isotopes!
- [ All Muttering ]

06:16.509 --> 06:20.343
<i>##[ All Singing Rock ]</i>

06:26.853 --> 06:29.083
- [ Screams ]
- Whoop. Careful.

06:30.690 --> 06:34.626
[ Munching ]
Wow. You look really hungover, Dad.

06:34.727 --> 06:36.627
What did you do last night?

06:36.729 --> 06:39.562
Last night? Um-

06:39.665 --> 06:42.930
<i>##[ Piano ]</i>

06:55.381 --> 06:57.076
<i>##[ Ominous Chord ]</i>

06:57.183 --> 07:00.084
Mm, uh, hello, big Maggie.

07:00.186 --> 07:02.017
<i>Yes.! Yes.! Yes.!</i>

07:02.121 --> 07:05.147
- Someone trashed the school!
- <i>What the ''dillio''?</i>

07:05.258 --> 07:08.659
Where this morning the three R's
stand for ''rowdiness''....

07:08.761 --> 07:11.525
''ransacking''
and ''e-responsibility.''

07:11.631 --> 07:13.531
- Any suspects, Chief?
- None.

07:13.633 --> 07:18.502
That's why we're jumping to the conclusion
that this was the work of no-good punk kids.

07:18.604 --> 07:20.970
- Kids?
- Therefore, effective immediately...

07:21.073 --> 07:23.166
I am imposing a curfew.

07:23.276 --> 07:27.076
Any kid caught on the street
after dark will be shot...

07:27.180 --> 07:30.638
or returned to their parents,
as the situation may warrant.

07:30.750 --> 07:32.843
- Whoa!
- Curfew?

07:32.952 --> 07:35.352
Serves you little punks right.

07:35.455 --> 07:39.016
Maybe next time you'll think
before- Oh, my God!

07:39.125 --> 07:43.562
Look what those rotten kids
did to my car!

07:47.800 --> 07:50.928
The cops can't just slap
a curfew on us! We have rights!

07:51.037 --> 07:54.438
Sure you do.
You have the right to remain silent.

07:54.540 --> 07:56.201
[ Both Laughing ]

07:56.309 --> 07:58.573
- That was cold-blooded, Marge.
- Yeah.

07:58.678 --> 08:01.875
But it's not fair. Adults always
blame kids for everything.

08:01.981 --> 08:05.439
Well, if kids are so innocent,
why is everything bad named after them?

08:05.551 --> 08:09.078
Acting childish,
kidnapping, child abuse.

08:09.188 --> 08:12.521
- What about adultery?
- Not until you're older, Son.

08:12.625 --> 08:14.923
[ Children Giggling ]

08:15.027 --> 08:16.927
Okay, go deep!

08:18.097 --> 08:20.998
- Ice cream truck!
- <i>[ Excited Shouting ]</i>

08:21.100 --> 08:23.591
I was here first!
Get out of my way!

08:23.703 --> 08:27.696
- ## [ Cheerful Tune ]
- [ Children Laughing ]

08:27.807 --> 08:30.435
<i>[ Siren Wailing ]</i>

08:30.543 --> 08:34.274
<i>Achtung,</i> babies!
Curfew is in effect!

08:34.380 --> 08:36.472
Return to your homes immediately.

08:36.582 --> 08:38.515
[ Screaming ]

08:38.618 --> 08:40.643
[ Boy Whining ]
I don't want to return home.

08:41.953 --> 08:44.217
All right. Let's see some I.D.'s, boys.

08:44.323 --> 08:47.588
[ Scoffs ]
You two scofflaws are violating curfew.

08:47.693 --> 08:49.752
I'm taking you downtown.

08:49.862 --> 08:52.422
Oh, uh, sorry to disturb you,
Dr. Hibbert.

08:52.532 --> 08:54.432
[ Deep Voice ]
Not at all, officer.

08:54.534 --> 08:57.503
[ Laughing ]

08:59.171 --> 09:03.107
Oh, what a beautiful night.
Fireflies, full moon-

09:03.209 --> 09:05.370
And here we are, locked inside.

09:05.478 --> 09:08.606
Kids, the carnival's in town
for one night only!

09:08.714 --> 09:11.182
And they've got cotton candy
and hats with feathers!

09:11.284 --> 09:13.912
And there's no lines, because
all the stupid kids have curfew!

09:14.020 --> 09:16.989
So- Oh, right. Sorry.

09:17.089 --> 09:19.956
[ Giggling ]

09:20.059 --> 09:22.960
[ Both Sighing ]

09:23.062 --> 09:25.826
Why don't you kids play
one of your old board games?

09:25.932 --> 09:28.799
When was the last time
you played Citizenship?

09:28.901 --> 09:31.335
- Energy Shortage?
- Hippo in the House?

09:31.437 --> 09:33.337
<i>[ Marge ]</i>
<i>Ooh, the Game of Lent.!</i>

09:33.439 --> 09:36.966
- [ Groans ] Can't we just go to bed?
- It's only 5:30.

09:37.076 --> 09:40.011
Fine. We'll play Hippo in the House.

09:40.112 --> 09:44.606
- Oh, the hippo's missing.
- [ Both Groaning ]

09:44.717 --> 09:48.983
You think that's bad.
I had to talk to my mom all night.

09:49.088 --> 09:52.615
She's got problems.
Scary problems.

09:52.725 --> 09:54.625
Adults blow.

09:54.727 --> 09:56.558
Yeah,just look at 'em over there.

09:56.662 --> 09:58.926
Smokin' their cigarettes.

09:59.031 --> 10:00.931
Drinkin' their coffee.

10:01.033 --> 10:02.933
Scratchin' their big butts.

10:03.035 --> 10:06.129
Your metabolism will change
someday too, young man.

10:06.238 --> 10:08.729
[ Mutters, Clears Throat ]

10:08.841 --> 10:11.708
<i>[ Motor Humming ]</i>

10:11.811 --> 10:16.441
That oughta show little Timmy and Tammy
Scumbag who's in charge around here.

10:16.549 --> 10:19.712
Gee, Chief, all those gears and motors
must've cost a fortune.

10:19.819 --> 10:23.152
-Well, you gotta spend money to make money, Lou.
-Mm-hmm.

10:24.690 --> 10:27.454
[ Yawns ]
You wanna hold it for a while?

10:27.560 --> 10:29.460
Nah.

10:29.562 --> 10:32.429
- ## [ Humming ]
- Marge, kite.

10:32.531 --> 10:34.522
Hey, there is one thing we could do.

10:34.634 --> 10:36.727
[ Gasps ]
Lise, no! It's prime time!

10:36.836 --> 10:39.031
You robbed me of my manhood!

10:39.138 --> 10:41.368
That's petty theft.

10:41.474 --> 10:44.238
- [ TVAudience ] Ooh!
- Don't go there.

10:44.343 --> 10:47.574
[ Laughing, Applause ]

10:47.680 --> 10:49.272
<i>Don't Go There</i> will be right back.

10:49.382 --> 10:52.283
- Oh, no it won't.
- <i>Wait.! There's a commercial.!</i>

10:52.385 --> 10:55.912
<i>[ Wolf Howling ]</i>

10:56.022 --> 10:58.047
- Oh, yeah.
- Whoa.

10:58.157 --> 11:01.058
- [ Wolves Snarling ]
- <i>[ Man Narrating ] Forty years ago...</i>

11:01.160 --> 11:04.220
<i>a film appeared that was</i>
<i>so shocking, so terrifying...</i>

11:04.330 --> 11:07.527
<i>it was sealed in a concrete</i>
<i>vault deep beneath the earth.</i>

11:07.633 --> 11:10.693
<i>But even the new management</i>
<i>of Sony TriStar...</i>

11:10.803 --> 11:14.068
<i>could not contain the pure evil</i>
<i>of...</i> The Bloodening.

11:14.173 --> 11:16.698
<i>[ Woman Screaming ]</i>

11:16.809 --> 11:18.640
Milhouse, do you see
what's on Channel 6?

11:18.744 --> 11:22.407
Uh, yeah. It's really something.
[ Screams ]

11:22.515 --> 11:26.007
- [ Screaming ]
- <i>A registered nurse trained</i>
<i>in the treatment of terror...</i>

11:26.118 --> 11:29.576
will be on duty during
the showing of <i>The Bloodening.</i>

11:29.689 --> 11:31.782
<i>[ Eerie Laughing ]</i>

11:31.891 --> 11:35.383
<i>[ TVAnnouncer ] Now playing</i>
<i>at the Springfield Drive-In... after dark.</i>

11:35.494 --> 11:38.588
Milhouse, spread the word.
We're seeing this movie tonight.

11:38.698 --> 11:42.099
That's right.
We're breaking curfew.

11:47.907 --> 11:49.807
Come on!

11:54.380 --> 11:57.577
- I'm breaking curfew, Mom!
- <i>[ Mother ] We're out of Skoal.!</i>

12:03.155 --> 12:06.090
''Due to the likelihood
of fear-induced heart attacks...

12:06.192 --> 12:09.855
we're offering all patrons
million-dollar life insurance policies.''

12:09.962 --> 12:13.523
Life insurance? Hmm. Will I be able
to borrow against the equity?

12:13.632 --> 12:16.123
I don't know, sir.
It comes free with the popcorn.

12:16.235 --> 12:18.135
- Is that air-popped?
- <i>Skinner.!</i>

12:18.237 --> 12:20.705
- We're losing valuable make-out time.
- [ Giggles ]

12:22.074 --> 12:25.237
[ Grunting ]
A little help.

12:25.344 --> 12:29.542
- Sure.
- [ Grunts, Groans ]

12:29.648 --> 12:33.015
- [ Grunts ] Lisa.
- Nelson.

12:33.119 --> 12:37.920
## [ Chorus Singing ]

12:39.825 --> 12:42.293
[ Wolves Howling ]

12:45.698 --> 12:48.030
Get off of my moor,
you mischievous weans!

12:48.134 --> 12:51.001
[ English Accent ]
Actually, we prefer to stay.

12:52.304 --> 12:54.932
You're thinking about hurting us.

12:55.040 --> 12:57.270
- [ Gasps ]
- Now you're thinking...

12:57.376 --> 12:59.503
''How did they know
what I was thinking?''

12:59.612 --> 13:03.878
Now you're thinking, ''I hope
that's shepherd's pie in my knickers.''

13:03.983 --> 13:05.450
[ Gasping ]

13:06.786 --> 13:09.254
[ Screaming ]

13:09.355 --> 13:11.255
- Wow!
- They showed him!

13:11.357 --> 13:14.724
Man, I never liked Shakespeare
until now.

13:14.827 --> 13:17.091
- [ Crowd Chattering ]
- Right, you little blighters.

13:17.196 --> 13:19.187
We've had quite enough
of your evil mischief.

13:19.298 --> 13:21.391
But you're the one who's been bad.

13:21.500 --> 13:23.400
You've been sneaking puddings.

13:23.502 --> 13:25.436
But- But how did you know?

13:25.538 --> 13:28.302
We know all your secrets.

13:28.407 --> 13:30.307
And you pilfered the poor box.

13:30.409 --> 13:33.071
- [ Gasps ]
- And, Doctor, we know
that you and the bootblack...

13:33.179 --> 13:37.081
<i>have been rogering the fishwife</i>
<i>in the crumpet shop.</i>

13:37.183 --> 13:38.878
- [ Gasps ] Lies!
- How dare you!

13:38.984 --> 13:41.384
Get them! Quickly!

13:41.487 --> 13:43.785
We can't have that.

13:46.992 --> 13:49.119
[ All Gasping ]

13:50.729 --> 13:54.096
[ All Grunting, Groaning ]

13:54.200 --> 13:56.532
<i>[ Screaming ]</i>

13:56.635 --> 13:58.603
- Take that, you suckers!
- Stick him with the pitchfork!

13:58.704 --> 14:01.332
- Way to go!
- In your face, fishwife!

14:02.741 --> 14:04.834
Enjoying the movie, kids?

14:04.944 --> 14:06.912
[ All Screaming ]

14:07.012 --> 14:10.311
Listen up, punks.
The moral of the story is...

14:10.416 --> 14:13.510
the adults always win.

14:13.619 --> 14:16.383
[ Screams ]

14:16.488 --> 14:19.355
For crying out loud, Eddie.
You scared the hell out of me.

14:19.458 --> 14:22.985
Sorry, Chief.
[ Chuckles ]

14:24.396 --> 14:28.230
[ Groaning ]

14:30.336 --> 14:32.634
Don't forget to clean under the jowls.

14:32.738 --> 14:35.002
That spot is Club Med for mildew.

14:36.342 --> 14:38.469
And let this be a lesson to you!

14:38.577 --> 14:42.604
Kids never learn!
[ Snickers ]

14:42.715 --> 14:45.343
[ Groaning, Coughing ]

14:45.451 --> 14:49.182
Oh, that is it! I'm tired of being
pushed around by grown-ups!

14:49.288 --> 14:51.279
It's time to fight back!

14:51.390 --> 14:54.018
- Yeah!
- Fight back! Fight back!

14:54.126 --> 14:57.254
Man, if we had eye power
like those kids in that movie...

14:57.363 --> 15:00.093
we could read the adults' mind
and tell their secrets...

15:00.199 --> 15:03.032
and make 'em pitchfork
each other and junk!

15:03.135 --> 15:05.433
- Oh, yeah!
- Wait!

15:05.537 --> 15:07.528
We don't need supernatural powers.

15:07.640 --> 15:09.608
We already know their secrets.

15:09.708 --> 15:12.836
She's right. Homer's done a ton of crap
that never made the papers.

15:12.945 --> 15:16.210
My mom shoplifts all the time.
Stuff she doesn't even need.

15:16.315 --> 15:19.045
My dad gets in car accidents
on purpose.

15:19.151 --> 15:21.051
Great.
This is all gold.

15:21.153 --> 15:23.553
[ Milhouse ]
We gotta spread this stuff around.

15:23.656 --> 15:25.556
Let's put it on the Internet!

15:25.658 --> 15:29.059
[ Bart ] No! We have to reach people
whose opinions actually matter.

15:29.161 --> 15:32.221
And I think I know how.
Why don't we-

15:32.331 --> 15:35.732
- I can get my dad's amplifier from the garage.
- Yeah, that's a good idea.

15:35.834 --> 15:38.598
Attention, hemline
and midriff monitors.

15:38.704 --> 15:40.899
- [ Glass Squeaking ]
- [ Gasps ]

15:41.006 --> 15:42.871
Willie, get my Windex!

15:44.576 --> 15:46.942
[ Snoring ]

15:50.816 --> 15:52.716
[ Cat Screeches ]

15:52.818 --> 15:56.515
200 channels,
nothin' but cats.

16:05.731 --> 16:09.360
So, Marge, ready for another
episode of <i>Don't Go There?</i>

16:09.468 --> 16:11.436
I'm tired of that show.

16:11.537 --> 16:14.802
But I've been hearing good things
about <i>Talk to the Hand.</i>

16:14.907 --> 16:18.399
Tom Shales says the writing
''snaps, crackles and pops.''

16:18.510 --> 16:20.705
Okay. Whatever takes
my mind off my life.

16:20.813 --> 16:23.748
## [ Chorus Singing ]

16:23.849 --> 16:27.649
Hey, look what I found!
Grampa's old radio.

16:27.753 --> 16:32.019
Oh, wouldn't it be grand
to gather round and have a listen?

16:32.124 --> 16:34.718
Well, turn something on.
I'm startin' to think!

16:34.827 --> 16:37.625
[ Changing Stations ]

16:38.998 --> 16:43.059
[ F.D.R.'s Voice ]
A date which will live in infamy.

16:43.168 --> 16:46.535
Good evening, adults.
We interrupt this broadcast...

16:46.638 --> 16:49.198
to bring you a very special
presentation.

16:49.308 --> 16:51.503
Tonight's program is entitled-

16:51.610 --> 16:54.841
[ Together]
<i>We Know All Your Secrets.</i>

16:54.947 --> 16:58.041
Boring! Go back to that ''infamy'' guy.

16:58.150 --> 17:01.210
[ Bart On Radio ]
Constable Wiggum likes to act tough...

17:01.320 --> 17:04.847
<i>but he also likes to walk the beat</i>
<i>in control-top panty hose.</i>

17:04.957 --> 17:07.517
- [ Both Gasp ]
- [ Chuckles ]

17:07.626 --> 17:10.424
Well, it's not like that's a crime.

17:17.069 --> 17:18.661
has been stealing supplies
from the school cafeteria.

17:18.771 --> 17:21.262
[ Gasps ]
Edna! How could you?

17:21.373 --> 17:24.273
Don't get up.
I'll bus my own tray.

17:26.211 --> 17:29.874
- And now we come to Mr. Homer Simpson.
- [ Screams ]

17:29.982 --> 17:33.645
Did you know he likes to eat
out of the Flanders' garbage?

17:33.752 --> 17:37.279
- Oh, Homer.
- I have a problem.

17:37.389 --> 17:40.654
Tune in tomorrow and every day
until the curfew is lifted...

17:40.759 --> 17:44.923
because we'll be revealing embarrassing
secrets about Springfield's other adults.

17:45.030 --> 17:47.362
Well, at least they've already done me.

17:47.466 --> 17:50.299
- And we have plenty more on Homer Simpson.
- D'oh!

17:50.402 --> 17:52.836
<i>I've called this meeting</i>
<i>to determine what to do...</i>

17:52.938 --> 17:56.567
about those blabbermouth kids
and their creepy English accents.

17:56.675 --> 17:59.235
Hey, shut up, Mayor!
They're tellin' secrets again!

17:59.344 --> 18:03.144
- [ Murmuring ]
- Oh, I hope they don't reveal this is a comb-over.

18:03.248 --> 18:08.276
[ Lisa With English Accent ] Our top secret
tonight- gay divorcee Luann Van Houten...

18:08.387 --> 18:11.845
<i>has been cheating</i>
<i>on her boyfriend, Pyro...</i>

18:11.957 --> 18:14.687
<i>with his best friend, Gyro.</i>

18:14.793 --> 18:17.421
How many times have I fought
beside you, Gyro?

18:17.529 --> 18:19.724
And this is how you repay me?

18:19.832 --> 18:23.928
- [ Both Grunting ]
- Pyro! Gyro! Settle down!

18:24.036 --> 18:27.403
Can't we shut down
that infernal transmitter?

18:27.506 --> 18:29.872
- Can't we just blow it up?
- You go ahead, girlfriend!

18:29.975 --> 18:32.637
- They're the worst!
- Yeah!

18:32.744 --> 18:35.406
- Say it again, girl!
- Settle down, people.

18:35.514 --> 18:39.109
As we speak, Chief Wiggum
is tracking down those little squealers...

18:39.218 --> 18:42.016
using the latest
in crime-fighting technology.

18:42.121 --> 18:45.215
Uh, I got nothing.
How about you, Frinky?

18:45.324 --> 18:49.488
I have captured the signal and am
presently triangulating the vectors...

18:49.595 --> 18:51.893
and compressing the data down...

18:51.997 --> 18:54.864
in order to express it
as a function of my hand.

18:54.967 --> 18:55.400
They're over there!

18:55.400 --> 18:55.889
They're over there!

19:02.141 --> 19:03.768
And guess who's been practicing
medicine without a license?

19:03.876 --> 19:06.436
- [ Gulps ]
- That's right. Homer Simpson.

19:06.545 --> 19:09.173
- <i>[ Homer ] D'oh.!</i>
- Freeze, you little shock jocks!

19:09.281 --> 19:11.647
[ Guns Cocking ]

19:15.554 --> 19:18.523
Brilliant. They transduced
amplitude modulation...

19:18.624 --> 19:22.424
via the concavity of that
oversized beverage conveyance.

19:22.528 --> 19:25.190
I mean, that is some clever ''viving.''

19:25.297 --> 19:27.390
All right, you kids,
come down now.

19:27.499 --> 19:30.059
- We promise we won't kill ya.
- Speak for yourself.

19:30.169 --> 19:34.196
Bart, get down here! I'm gonna
spank you back to the Stone Age!

19:34.306 --> 19:36.206
You can't make us come down!

19:36.308 --> 19:38.299
You adults are always
givin' us orders!

19:38.410 --> 19:40.173
You kids are always
disobeying them.

19:40.279 --> 19:42.804
Well, adults treat kids
like children!

19:42.915 --> 19:45.406
Kids treat adults
like cash machines!

19:45.517 --> 19:46.541
- Adults!
- Kids!

19:46.652 --> 19:47.641
- Adults!
- Kids!

19:47.753 --> 19:48.981
- Adults!
- Kids!

19:49.087 --> 19:52.079
## [ Singing Musical Comedy ]

19:52.191 --> 19:56.651
- ## [ Continues ]
- [ Marge Groans ]

20:19.351 --> 20:23.117
- ## [ Continues ]
- [ Cat Screeches ]

20:50.148 --> 20:52.514
- [ Screams ]
- ## [ Continues ]

21:01.393 --> 21:05.523
## [ Ends ]

21:07.633 --> 21:10.602
We're gonna teach
all you rug rats a lesson.

21:10.702 --> 21:14.729
Oh, yeah? What can you
old people do to us?

21:14.840 --> 21:17.570
- Yeah, you old fogeys!
- Buzz off, you old-

21:17.676 --> 21:19.576
- What do you got?
- You're all wrinkly!

21:19.678 --> 21:21.578
Somebody should iron you!

21:21.680 --> 21:25.138
This is Kent Brockman
reporting from... my own home...

21:25.250 --> 21:29.118
in accordance with the new
curfew for anyone under 7 0.

21:29.221 --> 21:32.019
- Mm, I can't believe that passed.
- [ Grumbling ]

21:32.124 --> 21:35.582
I warned you guys that seniors
always vote in record numbers.

21:35.694 --> 21:39.186
The controversial measure
passed by a single vote.

21:39.298 --> 21:41.766
[ Groans ]
You really should've voted, Homer.

21:41.867 --> 21:44.131
[ Scoffs ]
It wouldn't have made a difference.

21:44.236 --> 21:47.728
Lights out, you punk kids!

21:49.074 --> 21:52.942
Yea! We took back the night!

21:53.045 --> 21:55.878
Hey, fellas! Hey, you wanna
stop with the kicking?

21:56.982 --> 21:59.109
<i>My pills are in that can.!</i>

21:59.217 --> 22:03.278
<i>Good gravy.!</i>
<i>I don't kick your things.</i>

22:03.388 --> 22:07.324
<i>When you're trying to breathe</i>
<i>on the machine, do I go up and kick it?</i>

22:07.426 --> 22:10.327
<i>Oh, now look at that.</i>
<i>It went down the sewer.! You happy?</i>

22:10.429 --> 22:13.364
<i>I'm gonna sue now.!</i>
<i>Now it's time for the lawyers.!</i>

22:41.360 --> 22:45.763
- Shh.
- Don't tell me to shush, you stupid lady!

